com.opengamma.strata.product.credit.type

Interface IsdaYieldCurveConvention

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Named

    public interface IsdaYieldCurveConvention
extends Named
    CDS Standard model definition for parameters required to bootstrap an ISDA yield curve

    The ISDA conventions related to CDS Standard model deviate from the standard market conventions FixedIborSwapConvention.

    For instance, holiday calendars are generally ignored when building these curves (JPY is an exception) and only the fixed leg conventions are used (the floating leg details are ignored). Additionally, these conventions apply not just to the underlying swap instruments but also the money market instruments used to build the curve. This is why there is both a mmDayCount and a fixedDayCount.
